<div id="review_3568086985" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3568086985" />
    <a title="Meghan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9300205-meghan"><img alt="Meghan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1485788541p2/9300205.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3568086985?book_show_action=true">Sep 26, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Meghan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Meghan" href="/user/show/9300205-meghan">Meghan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3568086985" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2670692410369517402"><strong>Family matters</strong><br/><br/>This second book sees the community trying to pick up from book ones actions and ending, but many don’t believe it is over and that Nathan is still around. Danny comes back to search for him and falls for the girl he helped rescue, but she still has a few secrets. <br/><br/>The story is spread over a four day window and includes many secondary characters as well as some carry over characters from the last book. The descriptions of the kidnappings, purpose of them and the reactions are vivid </span>
  <span id="freeText2670692410369517402" style="display:none"><strong>Family matters</strong><br /><br />This second book sees the community trying to pick up from book ones actions and ending, but many don’t believe it is over and that Nathan is still around. Danny comes back to search for him and falls for the girl he helped rescue, but she still has a few secrets. <br /><br />The story is spread over a four day window and includes many secondary characters as well as some carry over characters from the last book. The descriptions of the kidnappings, purpose of them and the reactions are vivid and written where the emotion is tangible. The romance is a slow burn and there is perhaps a new romance introduced as well. The dogs play a good role and friendship/family is at the heart of it all. <br /><br />I enjoyed the ending and the characters, felt certain parts were predictable, and look forward to more of this family. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2670692410369517402" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


