<div id="review_3237092182" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3237092182" />
    <a title="Lynne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7768657-lynne"><img alt="Lynne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1517888921p2/7768657.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3237092182?book_show_action=true">Mar 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lynne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lynne" href="/user/show/7768657-lynne">Lynne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3237092182" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10768845229217625365"><strong>An excellent continuation of Midnight Exposure</strong><br/><br/>In the second book of the series, Danny goes back to Maine to make sure his sister’s abductor is dead so she can have peace of mind. He meets a woman named Mandy who runs her family’s inn the night her best friend was almost killed. Destiny brings Danny &amp; Mandy together and they will fight to save the ones they love. <br/>Another excellent read!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


